text: Macrozamia humilis is a species of plant in the family Zamiaceae. It is endemic to Inverell in New South Wales, Australia. Its natural habitat is on granite soils in temperate shrubby woodland forests. ==Sources== humilis Category:Endemic flora of Australia Category:Flora of New South Wales Category:Cycadophyta of Australia Category:Vulnerable flora of Australia Category:Taxonomy articles created by Polbot
